<Layout 
  title="Maine Issues First-Ever Medical Cannabis Patient Advisory After Unsafe Pesticide Levels Found in Concentrates" 
  description="Breaking: Maine's Office of Cannabis Policy issued its first medical cannabis patient advisory on January 22, 2026 after testing found unsafe pesticide levels in five cannabis concentrate strains sold by MarijuanaVille dispensary chain. The worst case: a concentrate with bifenthrin at 190 times the acceptable limit."
