        <p>"This advisory should be a wake-up call for the legislature. We have a 42% contamination rate in medical cannabis products, no testing requirements, and now a confirmed case of a patient harmed by pesticides. LD 1847 was the answer. It did not pass. The patients are still waiting."</p>
        <cite>— Patient safety advocate, speaking on condition of anonymity, April 2026</cite>
      </blockquote>
